## Acceptance Criteria

### AC1: All "Open full docs" links resolve to a rendered page

```
Given the dashboard is running
When a user opens any help popup and clicks "Open full docs →"
Then the browser navigates to /system/docs/{doc_slug} and returns HTTP 200
  with a styled HTML page rendering the relevant architecture document
```

### AC2: The docs_link mapping is centralised — no hardcoded hrefs in partials

```
Given the 22 help partial templates
When inspected for hardcoded /docs/ or /orch/ href values
Then none are found — all "Open full docs" links use {{ docs_link }}
  sourced from the _SLUG_TO_DOC dict in help.py
```

### AC3: Unknown doc slugs return 404 (directory traversal prevented)

```
Given the /system/docs/{doc_slug} route
When called with a slug not in the allow-list (e.g. /system/docs/../secrets)
Then the route returns HTTP 404 with no file content leaked
```

### AC4: The rendered page displays correct content for each mapped slug

```
Given the slug-to-doc mapping in help.py
When /system/docs/IW_AI_Core_Daemon_Design is requested
Then the response body contains content from docs/IW_AI_Core_Daemon_Design.md
  (e.g. a heading from that file)
```

### AC5: Heading anchors work (TOC extension active)

```
Given /system/docs/IW_AI_Core_CLI_Spec#approve is opened
When the page loads
Then the browser scrolls to the "approve" heading
  (heading IDs are generated by the toc extension)
```

